    • Method Detail

      • setAllowSshRootLogin

        public VsphereClusterNodeVMDeploymentConfig.Builder setAllowSshRootLogin(Boolean allowSshRootLogin)
        If true, the root user will be allowed to log into the VM. Allowing root SSH logins is not recommended for security reasons.
        Parameters:
        allowSshRootLogin - New value for the property.

      • setDefaultGatewayAddresses

        public VsphereClusterNodeVMDeploymentConfig.Builder setDefaultGatewayAddresses(List<String> defaultGatewayAddresses)
        The default gateway for the VM to be deployed must be specified if all the other VMs it communicates with are not in the same subnet. Do not specify this field and management_port_subnets to use DHCP. Note: only single IPv4 default gateway address is supported and it must belong to management network. IMPORTANT: Controllers deployed using DHCP are currently not supported, so this parameter should be specified for deploying Controllers. format: ip
        Parameters:
        defaultGatewayAddresses - New value for the property.

      • setDnsServers

        public VsphereClusterNodeVMDeploymentConfig.Builder setDnsServers(List<String> dnsServers)
        List of DNS servers. If DHCP is used, the default DNS servers associated with the DHCP server will be used instead. format: ipv4
        Parameters:
        dnsServers - New value for the property.

      • setEnableSsh

        public VsphereClusterNodeVMDeploymentConfig.Builder setEnableSsh(Boolean enableSsh)
        If true, the SSH service will automatically be started on the VM. Enabling SSH service is not recommended for security reasons.
        Parameters:
        enableSsh - New value for the property.

      • setHostId

        public VsphereClusterNodeVMDeploymentConfig.Builder setHostId(String hostId)
        The cluster node VM will be deployed on the specified host in the specified VC server within the cluster if host_id is specified. Note: User must ensure that storage and specified networks are accessible by this host.
        Parameters:
        hostId - New value for the property.

      • setManagementPortSubnets

        public VsphereClusterNodeVMDeploymentConfig.Builder setManagementPortSubnets(List<IPSubnet> managementPortSubnets)
        IP Address and subnet configuration for the management port. Do not specify this field and default_gateway_addresses to use DHCP. Note: only one IPv4 address is supported for the management port. IMPORTANT: Controllers deployed using DHCP are currently not supported, so this parameter should be specified for deploying Controllers.
        Parameters:
        managementPortSubnets - New value for the property.

      • setNtpServers

        public VsphereClusterNodeVMDeploymentConfig.Builder setNtpServers(List<String> ntpServers)
        List of NTP servers. To use hostnames, a DNS server must be defined. If not using DHCP, a DNS server should be specified under dns_servers. format: hostname-or-ipv4
        Parameters:
        ntpServers - New value for the property.
